Rating: 3
There are only 2 of us so when we buy a 1/2 turkey breast(3 lb) one has to get creative. No need for creativity with this recipe, though: on the unusual side and so full of flavor you wonder how it happened. My only potential change would have been the almonds, as I don't taste them in the dish; you could use other crunchy ingredients. Also found that the mop (or rub, depending on your definition) stuck readily to the first cutlet or two so I had to work a bit to get all cutlet pieces covered. The result was WONDERFUL

Rating: 4
I really enjoyed this recipe. It was fast and easy, and very flavorful. I followed the recipe as closely as possible, using an indoor grill because my outside grill ran out of gas while I was preheating. :) The exceptions I made were that I accidentally used too much salt, and I only had slivered almonds, so I chopped them up a bit before toasting. Adding the freshly toasted almonds to the sauce mixture brought out the flavors wonderfully. I thought that the sauce might go to waste because there was a lot of it, so I served the turkey over a salad of mixed baby greens, tomato wedges, thinly-sliced sweet onions, and a fresh cherry pepper. It was excellent all together.

